Because of their love
for Bashar al-Assad?

21:54.266 --> 21:56.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I don't think so.

21:56.333 --> 21:59.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have to think of what
is happening in Lebanon and
what are Hezbollah's concerns

21:59.300 --> 22:00.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for their own survival.

22:00.833 --> 22:05.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: The answer to
that question lies in geography.

22:05.400 --> 22:10.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Designated by foreign
governments as a terrorist
organization, Hezbollah
is blocked from using

22:10.333 --> 22:12.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the sea and air.

22:12.333 --> 22:16.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
To the south sits Israel,
with whom Lebanon is
still officially at war.

22:19.033 --> 22:21.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hezbollah's weaponry
and financing comes
from Iran, across
Shia-dominated Iraq, through

22:22.600 --> 22:24.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Syria and into Lebanon.

22:24.666 --> 22:29.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Shia axis, as it is often
called, would be broken if
the Sunni-dominated opposition

22:30.066 --> 22:32.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
took over Syria.

22:32.200 --> 22:36.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TIMUR GOKSEL: For them, survival
of the Syrian regime, a friendly
regime in Syria, is Hezbollah's

22:40.300 --> 22:41.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
existence.

22:41.300 --> 22:43.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's their survival.

22:43.233 --> 22:47.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: On the
battlefield in Syria, Hezbollah
has proved its effectiveness.

22:47.166 --> 22:52.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Those injured during battles in
Syria rely on the organization's
extensive network and

22:52.800 --> 22:54.866 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
assistance.

22:54.866 --> 22:58.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The "NewsHour" was given
exclusive access to
this Hezbollah treatment
center in Beirut,

23:00.933 --> 23:04.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
where the group's war wounded
from Syria received treatment
and physical therapy.

23:06.833 --> 23:09.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We were not allowed to
speak with these fighters,
but Imad Khoshman, who
lost a leg fighting

23:09.266 --> 23:14.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Israeli army in the past
and now runs the center, told
us about the kind of injuries

23:14.866 --> 23:16.900 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
he sees here.

23:16.900 --> 23:19.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
IMAD KHOSHMAN, Runs Treatment
Center (through translator):
They are normally very painful,

23:19.300 --> 23:22.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
such as spinal cord
injuries or in the brain.

23:22.100 --> 23:27.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They lead to a person being
paralyzed, not being able to
speak, not being able to move,

23:27.700 --> 23:30.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
or losing limbs.

23:30.200 --> 23:34.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: This young
fighter is recovering
from a devastating
head injury, struggling

23:36.866 --> 23:39.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to relearn names for
everyday objects.

23:39.733 --> 23:44.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
However, the war wounded are
just one type of patient here.

23:46.766 --> 23:49.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The center mostly offers
medical care to civilians
from the local community.

23:52.266 --> 23:57.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's all part of a policy
cultivated by Hezbollah's
leader, Hassan Nasrallah.

23:59.266 --> 24:02.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Since becoming the
group's leader in 1992
after Israel killed his
predecessor, Nasrallah

24:04.666 --> 24:07.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
has expanded Hezbollah as a
militant group, and supervised
the creation of extensive social

24:09.966 --> 24:14.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
programs for its community,
effectively creating a state
within a state inside Lebanon.

24:16.833 --> 24:21.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hezbollah runs its own schools,
medical facilities and even
sports clubs across Lebanon.

24:23.266 --> 24:27.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They may also be used to
control that society, too.

24:27.300 --> 24:31.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Andrew Exum was the top Middle
East policy official at the
Pentagon at the end of the

24:31.466 --> 24:34.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Obama administration
and he lived in Lebanon
for several years.

24:34.933 --> 24:36.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANDREW EXUM, Former U.S. Deputy
Assistant Secretary of Defense:
The services that Hezbollah

24:36.866 --> 24:41.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
provides to its constituency
are services that, quite
frankly, the Lebanese government

24:42.566 --> 24:45.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
has failed to
provide historically.

24:45.100 --> 24:49.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, so, you can't blame
Lebanon's Shia constituency
for accepting the services
provided by Hezbollah.

24:52.300 --> 24:57.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On the other hand, it creates
a real dilemma for them when
they -- if they were to think

24:57.200 --> 24:59.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
about ever moving
away from Hezbollah.

24:59.866 --> 25:04.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Hezbollah is
estimated to have lost over
1,300 fighters in the war, more

25:06.000 --> 25:08.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
than they ever lost
fighting Israel.

25:08.100 --> 25:12.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Most of these women have male
loved ones fighting in Syria.

25:12.133 --> 25:14.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This woman lost a son.

25:14.133 --> 25:18.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As the mother of a man
seen as a martyr, her
emotions are complicated.

25:18.533 --> 25:23.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator):
The feeling of my son
being martyred is powerful.

25:23.433 --> 25:28.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He will attain a high position
in heaven for what he did for
us and for our dignity, even

25:28.100 --> 25:30.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
though it is difficult.

25:30.000 --> 25:32.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Because he is my
child, it is difficult.

25:32.100 --> 25:36.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: To followers
of Hezbollah, this sacrifice
is not made for politics.

25:37.300 --> 25:39.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It is a religious duty.

25:39.800 --> 25:43.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that duty is absolute
devotion and loyalty to
the global Shia community's
guardian, regardless

25:45.366 --> 25:47.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of national boundaries.

25:47.433 --> 25:51.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Currently, that guardian is
Iranian cleric and supreme
Leader Ayatollah Khomeini.

25:54.500 --> 25:58.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hezbollah has taken Iran's
side in the region-wide
rift between Shia Iran
and Sunni Saudi Arabia.

26:00.700 --> 26:03.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And Syria's war is
part of that rift.

26:03.566 --> 26:08.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Saudi Arabia and Iran
back opposing sides in
the sectarian conflict.

26:10.900 --> 26:15.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
While Hezbollah's
supporters in Lebanon remain
loyal, its popularity in
Sunni countries across

26:17.133 --> 26:20.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Middle East, which had
risen after the 2006 war with
Israel, has now plummeted.

26:22.300 --> 26:26.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The group is now perceived
as killing Sunni civilians
inside Syria on Iran's request.

26:28.500 --> 26:32.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANDREW EXUM: They very much
played a role in the regime
tactics to isolate, surround

26:35.366 --> 26:40.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and starve out communities, and
the siege and ultimate fall of
Eastern Aleppo had Hezbollah's

26:43.666 --> 26:45.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
fingerprints all over it.

26:45.600 --> 26:50.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: But Hezbollah
claims it is fighting terrorists
in Syria and making sure

26:51.266 --> 26:53.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
they don't cross
over into Lebanon.

26:53.833 --> 26:57.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
IMAD KHOSHMAN (through
translator): Our fighters
are injured fighting
terrorists and protecting

26:57.666 --> 26:59.133 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
our borders.

26:59.133 --> 27:02.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They are protecting our people,
our villages and our towns.

27:02.933 --> 27:07.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: However, for
all it has lost in regional
popularity, the group has become

27:08.966 --> 27:11.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
hugely strengthened militarily.

27:11.400 --> 27:16.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it is capitalizing on
that by pursuing further
involvement in the region.

27:16.366 --> 27:21.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The group is also fighting
in Iraq, taking on the
Sunni extremists ISIS.

27:23.366 --> 27:26.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At the same time, the U.S.-led
coalition is also fighting
the Islamic State in Iraq, and

27:28.166 --> 27:31.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
operating on the same
side as Shia militias,
including Hezbollah.

27:31.666 --> 27:36.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This indirect relationship
of convenience is an irony of
the war against the Islamic

27:36.433 --> 27:38.533 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
State.

27:38.533 --> 27:42.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The Trump administration
has talked tough about
containing Iran, but
given little explanation

27:44.466 --> 27:47.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of how it would play a role in
curbing Iran and its ally here
in Lebanon Hezbollah, while

27:49.100 --> 27:52.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
continuing to fight the
common enemy of ISIS.

27:52.866 --> 27:57.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
America has long viewed
Hezbollah as a terrorist
organization and a deadly enemy.

28:00.466 --> 28:03.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In 1983, the group killed
241 U.S. servicemen in
Lebanon when it blew up
a U.S. Marine barracks.

28:07.066 --> 28:10.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Israel is anxiously watching
Hezbollah's evolution.

28:10.033 --> 28:15.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Israeli military
has conducted airstrikes
against Hezbollah targets
inside Syria throughout

28:16.933 --> 28:21.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the war, although that hasn't
stopped the group from expanding
its arms supplies, which

28:22.100 --> 28:24.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
could threaten Israel.

28:24.200 --> 28:28.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In February, Hezbollah leader
Nasrallah leader threatened to
strike a nuclear facility in

28:29.066 --> 28:31.133 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Israel.

28:31.133 --> 28:33.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HASSAN NASRALLAH, Hezbollah
Leader (through translator):
They know that, if rockets hit

28:33.400 --> 28:36.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
this reactor, what would
befall them and their entity.

28:36.066 --> 28:39.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
They are aware of the
risks which would be
inflicted on them.

28:39.000 --> 28:44.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANE FERGUSON: Both Israel and
Hezbollah know a war between
them will bring more devastation

28:45.366 --> 28:49.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
than ever before for
communities on each side.

28:49.066 --> 28:53.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
This, for now, seems to
be the most effective
conflict prevention.

28:53.933 --> 28:58.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It is not one, however,
guaranteed to keep
this fragile truce.

28:58.633 --> 29:03.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm Jane
Ferguson in Beirut, Lebanon.

29:11.733 --> 29:16.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: As we mentioned
at the top of the program,
President Trump's agenda hit

29:21.033 --> 29:26.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
