that they view him as
someone with integrity.

31:19.433 --> 31:24.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he's the person who said
the president lied about the
situation at the FBI, and he

31:25.900 --> 31:29.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
was afraid the president would
also lie about their meeting.

31:29.166 --> 31:33.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHRISTOPHER RUDDY: Look, I think
Director Comey is a good guy,
but I also think he violated

31:33.900 --> 31:38.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
bureau policy when he
held a press conference
explaining why he wasn't
going to indict Hillary

31:40.066 --> 31:42.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Clinton back in
June of last year.

31:42.066 --> 31:43.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The FBI doesn't indict people.

31:43.666 --> 31:45.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They just -- they're an
investigative agency.

31:45.500 --> 31:47.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I'm not sure why he gave
that press conference.

31:47.800 --> 31:52.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think he violated FBI rules
when he interfered in the
election two weeks before.

31:54.266 --> 31:55.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He opened an investigation
into Hillary's e-mails.

31:55.833 --> 31:58.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The Democrats were very angry.

31:58.133 --> 32:03.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think he violated FBI rules
again last week when he admitted
he leaked confidential documents

32:05.033 --> 32:09.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
he compiled as the FBI
director to The New York Times.

32:09.766 --> 32:14.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some people say that might
have been ethically very
bad, but also possibly
a criminal violation.

32:18.033 --> 32:23.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I just think that he
engaged in a very unusual
pattern of activity.

32:25.000 --> 32:28.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm not saying that everything
the president has done has
been right in this case, but

32:30.600 --> 32:33.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
when you look at the facts,
you have to wonder, who
would you trust more here?

32:33.700 --> 32:38.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, you
mentioned the special
counsel, Robert Mueller.

32:38.100 --> 32:43.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And you suggested -- I think I
heard you suggesting that there
is a question about the purpose

32:43.833 --> 32:45.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of his investigation.

32:45.866 --> 32:49.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I want to ask you about
that, because there
are some Republicans
out there saying that

32:49.133 --> 32:51.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Robert Mueller shouldn't
be doing this job.

32:51.233 --> 32:56.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Is President Trump prepared
to let the special counsel
pursue his investigation?

32:58.133 --> 33:01.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHRISTOPHER RUDDY: Well, I
think he's considering perhaps
terminating the special counsel.

33:03.766 --> 33:08.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think he's weighing that
option, I think it's pretty
clear by what one of his lawyers

33:08.466 --> 33:10.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
said on television recently.

33:10.566 --> 33:15.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I personally think it would
be a significant mistake, even
though I don't think there is

