JUDY WOODRUFF: You don't think
there is a justification for?

33:22.766 --> 33:24.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHRISTOPHER RUDDY: For a
special counsel in this case.

33:24.400 --> 33:27.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But also -- I mean,
Robert Mueller, there
are some real conflicts.

33:27.833 --> 33:32.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
He comes from a law firm
that represent members
of the Trump family.

33:32.733 --> 33:37.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He interviewed the day before,
a few days before he was
appointed special counsel with

33:39.666 --> 33:42.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the president, who was
looking at him potentially to
become the next FBI director.

33:44.166 --> 33:46.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That hasn't been
published, but it's true.

33:46.266 --> 33:51.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And I think it would be
strange that he would
have a confidential
conversation, and then,

33:51.000 --> 33:56.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a few days later, become
the prosecutor of the person
he may be investigating.

33:57.966 --> 34:01.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think that Mueller shouldn't
have taken the position if
he was under consideration

34:01.733 --> 34:06.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and had a private meeting with
the president and was privy
maybe to some of his thoughts

34:08.133 --> 34:10.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
about that investigation or
other matters before the bureau.

34:10.200 --> 34:14.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, you know
for a fact that Robert Mueller
was offered another position

34:14.100 --> 34:16.200 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
before he became
special counsel?

34:16.200 --> 34:19.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
CHRISTOPHER RUDDY: I
know for a fact that he
was under consideration
and that the president

34:19.666 --> 34:23.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
did talk with him in
the days before he was
named special counsel.

34:23.266 --> 34:25.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I think there's
a conflict there.

34:25.333 --> 34:30.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Look, my position is that
Mueller is a man of integrity,
but we all know in the history

34:32.200 --> 34:37.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of these special investigations,
they go far and wide, and
they go well beyond what the

34:37.966 --> 34:39.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
original jurisdiction was.

34:39.933 --> 34:44.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's bringing in some of the
top prosecutors that have worked
in the Justice Department.

34:44.233 --> 34:47.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is not going to be
rosy for the White House.

34:47.133 --> 34:51.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I have to look at -- when
you say there's no -- Judy, I
think we both have to agree,

34:51.566 --> 34:53.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
so far, there's been no
evidence of wrongdoing.

34:53.733 --> 34:58.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's been no allegation
that the president engaged in
wrongdoing or any member of his

34:58.666 --> 35:00.266 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
staff did.

35:00.266 --> 35:02.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Let me ask you
one other thing, Chris Ruddy.

35:02.300 --> 35:07.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that is, the president's
declined so far to say one
way or the other whether there

35:09.166 --> 35:13.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
